Vol / Page:  99
Edition:
Quote:  TREVALLI (<i>Caranx Georgianus</i>). ... Dr. Hector says: `The trevalli is the arara of the Maoris, or trevalli or cavalli of the fishermen.' <i>Ibid.</i> 99 [quoting Hector <i>op. cit</i>.] Trevalli or cavalli of the fishermen ... In Auckland it is sometimes called yellow-tail, but this name appears to be also used for the king-fish. The fish known as trevalli in the Dunedin market is a different fish, allied to the warehou. [<i>Neptonemus brama</i>]
